@NODE "Histoire" "Histoire De BlitzBank"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}7. Blitzbank history@{ub}@{uu}

N= New version.
B= Corrected bug.
E= Option improved.
X= Removed option.

@{b}Version 1.0 ----> Version 1.1@{ub}

N - Printing bug  -> asking number of lines and columns.
E - IFF saving of stick statistics.
B - Correction of small display bug in credits and debits (-128.8999)
E - Displaying "Retrait"(withdrawal) or "Depot" (deposit) instead of a blank in column "category"
    of debits and withdrawals.
B - Bug corrected when pasting a depot or a withdrawal.
B - Bug corrected in statistics (did not take care of operations being validated)
E - Copy / paste with big blocks were too slow  -> dichotomous insertion and heap sort.
B - Error when calculating centimes from big numbers  -> centime precision up to 21 474 836.47 !
N - New option paste and move.
B - Bug corected when modifying validation or category of a depot or withdrawal operation.
B - Statistics displaying did not appear from year 2000.
N - Now possible to navigate in accounts using keyboard arrows.
E - Scrolling twice as fast.
E - Now possible to scroll on categories in pie-chart statistics.
N - Recognition and loading of files in ABank format.
E - New method of saving twice as economic with coding of password, dates and amounts.
N - Now possible to load an account by clicking on project-type icons.
    This icon is created at each saving of accounts if it does not already exist.
N - Creation of demonstration tool.
B - Screenmode different from PAL did not open  -> Bug corrected.

@{b}Version 1.1 ----> Version 1.2@{ub}

N - AGA palette support.
N - Now possible to move and close all windows thanks to the "CloseGadget".
E - New follow-up mode of automatic operations, with management of number of transfers to do.
N - Management and follow-up of bank or personnal borrowings.

@{b}Version 1.2 ----> Version 1.3@{ub}

B - BlitzBank's screen sometimes open with strange colors --> Bug corrected (DRIPens config...)
N - BlitzBank can now be installed in french or in english (doc is not in english)
B - Previous versions did not always recognize Abank file format. It was due to format
    change between versions. ABank files are now recognized whatever the version is.

@{b}Version 1.3 ---> Version 1.4@{ub}

B - Bug coming up when sorting dates corrected.
N - Use of locale.library (french catalog furnished).
N - Use of reqtools.library, allowing good-looking requesters more useful.
B - A guru sometimes happened at BlitzBank start.

@{b}Version 1.4 ---> Version 1.5@{ub}

B - ABank files containing empty categories were not correctly loaded in BlitzBank.
B - When categories were too numerous, statistics printed question marks due to an overflow.
    It's now possible to have up to 50 categories without problems.
N - Added a menu in pie-chart statistics to directly select the good month.
B - Version 1.4 used to crash when using bank borrowings.

@{b}Version 1.5 ---> Version 1.51@{ub}

N - Automatic detection of user's system (AGA or not, sys 2.0 or 2.1+...)
N - BlitzBank now indicates to the user files needed at startup if not found.
    ( it was used to result in a GURU )
B - BlitzBank cannot work without AGA chipset since version 1.2 !!
    B - A little bug with some ABank files now corrected.
E - Pie-charts statistics display now much faster (3 times as fast as ABank).
N - Now possible to move pie-charts statistics window.
N - Added 'Cancel' button in exit requester et displaying a requester when closing last
    account in memory.
B - A gap occured between pie-chart statistics colors and those from categories list when
    they were too numerous.
B - BlitzBank did not work without Xen.font font.
N - Now possible to put some lines 'off category'.
N - Function implementation allowing the user to import his own logos.
N - Automatic alphabetical sorting of logos.
B - A GURU occured when trying to modify a category and no one was in memory.
N - Now possible to sort categories in wished order by using functions like sort, move
    up / down ...
B - When a balance was null, it was written as 0.0 (and not 0.00), causing some little
    bugs thereafter.

@{b}Version 1.51 ---> Version 1.52@{ub}

X - Removal of demo tool (using too much memory and not very useful)
B - A bug occured when moving lines with "paste and move" while months total excedeed 12.
    Now possible to move 12, 20 or even 100 months if wished.
B - Version 1.51 used to crash when saving statistics.
B - BlitzBank crashed at startup if you saved preferences after having set screenmode
    using the "change mode" button in screenmode window.
N - Account lines display with very selective filter. ( you can for example just display
    january credits of year 1995, or in another hand just just display operations whose
    category is "thing" during the same month of the same year.
N - Graphical printing of pie-chart and stick statistics.
N - "Progress" option that allows to display a progress indicator for long tasks.
X - BlitzBank cannot longer read BlitzBank V1.0 accounts.
    BlitzBank V1.0 accounts were saved in ASCII files causing problems with ASCII files
    that weren't accounts !! Blitzbank now recognizes accounts files from other files.
E - Character number for designations is now 100 ( instead of 40 )
N - New tool "Insert". It allows to insert lines from another account.
B - Password detection didn't work.
B - A lot of little bugs have been wiped out.

@{b}Version 1.52 --> Version 1.53@{ub}

B - Lines validation gave balnace errors since version 1.52.
B - When opening BlitzBank without account in memory, current account didn't exist, but
    you were still able to add operations to this account.
    Unfortunately, if you choosed to open another account, the actual account was deleted
    because the computer thought there was no one!!

@{b}Version 1.53 --> Version 2.0a@{ub}

B - Scrolling produced a big error with wide screenmodes.
B - When modifying something, the display did not came back on the good line.
E - User interface has been modified and improved in ergonomics.
N - Total credits and debits are now calculated on displayed lines.
N - It is no< possible to obtain little assessed statistics and informations by pressing
    the cycle button of screen.
B - An overflow produced a GURU when moving lines with a selection.
N - Now possible to enter date with mouse's help ( like in Workbench prefs ).
N - When you add a new operation, you can now use designation from another operation
    in memory.
N - You can now hide all account balances with a simple mouse click.
    This allows you to keep your work safe from prying eyes.
E - Iconification now works whatever font you use for Workbench.
N - Transfers (automatic or not) are now possible with a predefined operation.
B - Small bug correction on loan dates.
B - Monthly period (default one) of automatic operations was not saved correctly.
B - Iconification sometimes caused a sytem jamming.
N - When clicking on the iconification close gadget, a requester asks you if you want to
    uniconify or quit.
B - The 'Cancel' option from palette choice window did not work correctly.
B - Categories were not correctly initialized, causing recording errors.
    Some categories were not correctly recorded by Blitzbank.
B - Palette sometimes caused GURU on 2.xx systems. This was due to a BlitzBasic bug which
    has been corrected later. I thank the author for it...
B - Sums below 1 were forgiven...
B - If a designation length was too big, a display bug occured.
E - Display filters are now initialized to zero after loading or changing account.

@{b}Version 2.0a --> Version 2.0b@{ub}

B - One of the display filters window cycle gadgets was not correctly initialized.
B - When more than a year of account was in memory, you were not abled to select the
    year at printing.
E - More aestetic menus because similar items have been put together.
N - A new display filter is available. This time it's on operations designation.
E - The default year was 1995 when loading an ABank account. Now it's current year.
E - Iconify option has been moved in the project menu (as usually).
E - Main window now frozen if another is opened. It avoids clicking on main window's
    buttons and interfering with the other one.
N - Used pointers are now those from system.
B - Categories sorting made a difference between upper-case and lower case charecters.
B - The last account entry remained last after an insertion.
E - 3D selection is smaller and doesn't hide upper and lower lines anymore.
E - Gadgets have been redrawn and look better.

@{b}Version 2.0b --> Version 2.0c@{ub}

N - Now possible to start Blitzbank with more than one argument. It allows several accounts
    in memory at Blitzbank startup.
B - A GURU occured when saving iconification position in a big workbench and then trying to
    reiconify in a smaller workbench.
N - BlitzBank now looks for modified accounts and ask user if he wants to save an account
    before quiting, closing or loading.
E - A busy pointer has been added during loading and saving.
B - There was a little display bug since version 2.0a.

@{b}Version 2.0c --> Version 2.0d@{ub}

X - Playing music ability has been dropped. The routine created problems with multitasking.
    Lots of GURU occured. Moreover, it was not essential and it saves 80 Ko of memory !!
B - A bug arised for 01/01/97 date. This bug is due to blitzbasic which returns 32/12/96 for
    this date. It makes crash the dates choice window with mouse. This bug is bypassed with
    a test for this date.
E - accounts logos have been revisited.
E - Lines display doesn't need screen refresh anymore. It allows display speedup and a
    flickerless scrolling.
N - Now possible to do a page up/down by using a combination of SHIFT + cursor arrows. You
    can also go directly to the account start/end with ALT + cursor arrows.
N - You can now choose the first month for yearly balance (not necessarily January) and you
    can calculate this balance with filters (for example display yearly balance for just one
    category...)
E - When adding an operation (automatic or not), list selector vanishes if you choose a
    predefined operation. Actually, it is useless when displayed category is going to be the
    default category for predefined operation (for example: deposit).
E - Inverted debits and credits columns for standardization.
B - Version 2.0c had a bug when loading Blitzbank with several accounts:
    accounts categories were inverted and you had to change account one time to have everything
    back in order.
E - Now possible to reach 150 categories (instead of 50).
B - Categories edition included two bugs since version 1.52:
       - If you got two empty categories in an account, it could cause a GURU.
       - When deleting a category, everything was fine but displayed categories didn't match
         those in memory.
N - New option: automatic operation with sum requester.
E - Files & screenmode ASL requesters have been replaced by reqtools requesters.
B - If you did 'Cancel' after 'Open & load', The program switched to the first account on not to
    the actual one.
B - Transfers made some account lines disappear and sometimes didn't found the target account.
E - Change in printing window: you can now select filters like display filters.
N - A header has been added at printing.
B - Resuming a category didn't always work and sometimes caused a GURU.
B - The date and designation choice window caused a big bug in automatic operation modification.
B - Designation length didn't fit correctly with column length.
E - Amigaguide documentation improvement.

@{b}Version 2.0d --> Version 2.0e@{ub}

N - Now possible to start Amigaguide documentation as a background task with a blitzbank
    menu or with HELP key.
E - More stability and enforcer hits removed.
B - A bug occured when loading big pictures with 'Import logo'.
E - Pie-charts statistics optimization : calculations are twice as fast as before.
B - Little display bug since version 2.0d with resolution height that are a multiple of  8.
B - Stick statistics didn't always match the good month.
B - It was impossible to load an account with more than 150 lines since version 2.0d !!

@{b}Version 2.0e --> Version 2.0f@{ub}

B - Little display bugs occured since version 2.0d (when validation or scrolling)
N - Now possible to calculate pocket amount on every accounts in memory. This option finally
    allows owners of several accounts to use pocket amount (it was hard to do before).
E - Improvement of Amigaguide documentation.

@{b}Version 2.0f --> Version 2.1@{ub}

N - Yearly previsionnal budget gestion.
E - Add a vertical icons toolbar when screen width exceeds 672 points.
N - Again possible to play music module but it now works perfectly with multitasking and it uses
    protracker format.
E - Commentaries (operations with null sum) are now displayed with a color choosen by the
    user. A blank will appear in debit/credits and category columns of such an operation.
B - Little display bug with english version.
E - Restructuring of 'preferences' menu.
N - BlitzBank now owns a message port : if BlitzBank is launched a second time and the first
    one is still resident, files in argument will be opened by the first one. For example, if you
    double-click an account icon and on another account one, the second account will
    automatically be opened with the first Blitzbank.
B - If one clicked on an account icon which was in "BlitzBank:" directory, the program cannot
    find this account (you had to load it with 'load' option).
    It was the same with DirectoryOpus which launched BlitzBank in WorkBench mode.
B - If you clicked on 'Cancel' in "Save under", account name was deleted.
E - Two gadgets "+" and "-" have been added to change year simplier in date edition window.
B - Real balance didn't take care of the fact that the pocket could be shared between several
    accounts : it is equal to bank-balance + pocket + operations_being_validated and when the
    pocket was shared, Blitzbank just added current account pocket.
N - You can now choose two ways to calculate the real balance :
        1- real balance = bank balance + pocket + operations_beeing_validated (old method)
        2- real balance = bank balance + operations_beeing_validated.
N - After each save, a .bak file is created. It allows to go back to last account if an error occurs.
B - Filter disply didn't work properly for year. If one choosed year 1995, it was always displayed
    "all account years".
B - An error occured if a category bigger than 127 was choosen.

@{b}Version 2.1 --> Version 2.15@{ub}

E - BlitzBank now has is version number directly in the executable. It allows Workbench's
    "version" command to be used to see Blitzbank's version number.
E - Installer script improved (it does the assign alone with no need to reboot and detects if
    BlitzBank is already installed and what is the version number).
B - Two or three bugs corrected that occured in 800*600 (super72).

@{b}Version 2.15 --> Version 2.16@{ub}

B - No more enforcer hits in BlitzBank.
B - The problem with 68000 should be solved now. (GURU)
B - When trying to modify an automatic operation with a long designation, the designation
    came out of the cycle gadget.

@{b}Version 2.16 --> Version 2.17@{ub}

N - Now possible to automatically insert year, month or week's day in designation with %m, %y
    and %d symbols.
E - You can now choose year directly with a menu, like you choose the month in some other
    functions.
B - A bug occured if one tried to modify an automatic withdrawal operation.
B - Cancel didn' t work when manipulating automatic operations !!
B - Cycle gadget was not updated after an automatic operation modification.

@{b}Version 2.17 --> Version 2.18@{ub}

B - A space voluntarily appeared in categories.
E - Installer script improvement: and update doesn't delete BlitzBank.prefs and doesn't ask for
    an insertion in user-startup anymore.
E - New icons were kindly send to me by Mr Peugnet and replaced the old ones.
B - Lines sometimes appeared on the text. They seem to have disappeared (use of
    SetSoftStyle system function instead of WindowFont function from Blitz).
E - Printing improvement : BlitzBank takes care of Workbench preferences and handles single
    sheet and continuous paper.

@{b}Version 2.18 --> Version 2.20@{ub}

E - Data types improved (20% faster and more economic with memory)
E - Up to 3000 operations for an account instead of 1850.
E - Dynamic memory allocation. No more total allocation at start.
E - Memory test : BlitzBank doesn't crash anymore if an operation hasn't enough memory but
    a requester tells the user about the problem.
B - The first account operation wasn't correctly saved if the account owns no categories.
E - Accounts loading twice as fast with the use of a cache system.

@{b}Version 2.20 --> Version 2.21@{ub}

B - When trying to scroll an operation text, a big display bug occured since version 2.20.
B - Display did'nt work for sums lower than 10 centimes. Display format gestion has been
    improved and simplified (5 Ko won on the executable).
B - An overflow occured nd caused a guru from 2000 operations. BlitzBank now really accepts
    3000 operations per account.
B - Commentaries printing caused a shift problem.

@{b}Version 2.21 --> Version 2.25@{ub}

E - New file saving version. Accounts from older versions can be loaded but older versions of
    Blitzbank will not be able to load accounts saved with this new version.
B - Some enforcer hits appeared after version 2.20.
E - Not possible anymore to create the first account without opening another one. It solves
    some memory bugs and makes comprehension easier.
B - GURUS occured with some functions if an account wasn't loaded since version 2.20.
B - Some little printing bugs have been corrected.
E - A 'Cancel' allows to stop printing between two pages .
B - The printing didn't take care of margins preferences.

@{b}Version 2.25 --> Version 2.29@{ub}

N - Spreading operations gestion.
N - Importation and exportation of QIF format (accepted by Quicken and Microsoft Money)
E - BlitzBank tests for each function if you have enough memory to make it run.
E - A link to budgetary forecast has been added to categories edition.
E - Audio channels are now tested before playing a module. So BlitzBank will never interact
    with another player.
E - A message is displayed when the documentation cannot be opened.
E - Categories display order in pie-charts statistics now respects the order choosen in categories
    edition.
B - Verification of defective memory.
B - BlitzBank doesn't always go back to the good line after an operation.
B - When adding an operation, the default category (the first one) was not correctly selected at
    start. You had to click on it.
B - The closing gadget for budgetary forecast didn't work.
B - There was sometimes a zero in front of dates numbers below 10 (05 déc 95).
B - Insertion worked, but inverted operations order with the same date.
B - The "Open new" option sometimes produced a GURU.
B - Accounts numbers "unnamed" weren't always correct.
B - When jumping from december to january in the date capture window, the year increased but of you
    jumped from january to december (using SHIFT), the year didn't decreased.
B - The palette was correctly saved in preferences, but was not correctly handled by BlitzBank.
    It was not really possible to change the palette.
B - Accounts insertion sometimes made categories and budgetary forecast crash...
B - Interference lines seem to have finally disappeared.

@{b}Version 2.29 --> Version 2.30@{ub}

E - Menus are now gadtool. More frendly, they add separators.
E - Week day now appears in date selector.
E - An error message appears when documentation cannot be loaded.
E - Great improvements in Installer script which automatically fits the language.
E - New bank logos have been added.
E - Yearly balance is much faster to display and horizontal lines allows to see the scale easily.
E - Yearly balance scale is now round allowing a faster reading.
E - In yearly balance the year increases when jumping from december to january and decreases when
    jumping from january to december.
E - The "About" option has been improved.
B - The  %m,%d,%y weren't adapted at printing.
B - BlitzBank sometimes crashes when jumping from an account to another.
B - The new BlitzBasic libraries seem to be very stable and BLtitzbank too :
    I don't have crashes anymore.
B - BlitzBasic bug on date 01/01/1997 wa back and displayed 32/12/96 !
B - When there was no operation in account two GURUS occured in statistics and when using cycle gadget.
B - The yearly balance didn't take care of internal spreadings.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "futur" "BlitzBank Futur"

Here are the things that are currently on study for a future version of BlitzBank:

1  Put a backdrop button in main window.
2  Gadgets personnalisation.
3  Categories groups gestion.
4  Share portfolio gestion.
5  New statistics
7  Borrowings calculation improvement after spreading (inspired by MONEY).
9  Put week's day in dates capture.
10 increase sums precision up to 1 milliard.
11 Edit all palette possible.
12 Click on validate column to validate a line.
13 Put a MagicWB backdrop. (not so easy...)
14 Font choice (graphic interface to rethink...)
15 Add bank cards gestion (automatic validation following several criteria).
16 Add one or two columns : operation type (check, CB, ...) and number (for example statement number)

Attention, those things are under study and if some of them are under developpement,
others will perhaps never be.

@ENDNODE


