@NODE "Comptes" "Comptes"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{u}@{b}3.6 Comptes@{uu}@{ub}

  This menu allows you to choose current account.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "l'écran" "L'Ecran De BlitzBank"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}2.Blitzbank screen@{uu}@{ub}

  BlitzBank's screen is splitted in several parts :

  To the left you can found :

      - bank balance : tells you the exact amount you have at the bank.

      - real balance : it gives you the balance taking care of non validated bank operations. A non
        validated operation is either a classical non validated bank operation or an operation with
        cash or an operation with your portfolio.
        You can choose from preferences the option to@{"Add pocket" LINK "Préférences" 36},
        to calculate the real balance amount using two different methods (considering pocket or not).

      - pocket : indicates the amount in your portfolio (meaning the amount of cash you have in
        your "pocket" at this time).
        It is the operation : real balance - bank balance - operations beeing validated.
        The option @{"Share pocket" LINK "Préférences" 30} from the "Preferences" menu
        allows to calculate the pocket on every account in memory.

  To the right you can find your bank and account icons.
  A cycle gadget allows you to choose which little information you want to see in the
  appropriate box. You can choose to see :

      - firstname and lastname of account's titular, account number and type.

      - Little average statistics from current account.

      - Little global statistics from current account.

      - Current display filter.

  In the lower part of the screen are the columns necessary to all accounts gestion program.
  Validated operations have the mark symbol, non validated operations don't have a symbol.
  Operations beeing validated have the half hidden mark symbol. You can scroll account lines
  using the scroller or keyboard arrows (SHIFT key combined with corsor arrows do a page jump
  and the ALT key combined with cursor arrows jumps to the begin / end of account)

  Screen features several icons that allows you to access options with a simple mouse clic. If
  your screen width exceeds 672 points, you'll have five new icons arranged vetically. In another
          case, only the horizontal icon toolbar will appear.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "éditer" "Editer"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}3.2 Edit@{ub}@{uu}

   - @{b}validate@{ub} : activate validation mode. This mode allows you to validate a line byt
     clicking on it. (the third gadget does the same).

   - @{b}modify@{ub} : activate modification mode. This mode allows you to modify date,
     nature, category or credit / debit of a line just by clicking on it. (4th gadget does the same)

   - @{b}select@{ub} : activate selection mode. This mode allows you to select one or
     several lines in order to do cut- copy-paste operations.(5th gadget does the same)

   - @{b}Add@{ub} : add an operation to the current account (1st gadget does the same)
     A window opens asking you :

        - the date (jjmmaa) that will be analysed and validated by the program.
          examples: you enter 320195 , it will become 010295;
                    you enter 000395 , it will become 280295.
          By clicking on the magnifier you can choose the date with the mouse according to a
          perpetual calendar :

        - operation nature.
          It is possible to display astonishing things with the help of following shorrtcuts :
             - %d: it will insert week's day corresponding to operation's date;
             - %m: it will insert month corresponding to operation's date;
             - %y: it will insert year corresponding to operation's date;
          those shortcuts allow you for example to insert "MONTH OF..." at each month beginning
          thanks to an automatic monthly operation; desired month will be automatically inserted
          each time :  "MONTH OF %m %y"; you can also choose to recall an old designation by
          clicking on the magnifier.

        - credit\debit (1st is positive, 2nd is negative)
          if you want to enter a comment line, this value has to be null. Then it will be displayed in
          the color you choosed in the @{"Preferences" LINK "préférences" 10} menu.

        - the category (choose it in categories list).

        - @{b}Validation@{ub}: Click on the cycle gadget to choose between "non validated
          operation", "operation beeing validated" or  "validated operation" .
          "Non validated operation" corresponds to an operation done with cash; it doesn't appear
          in bank operations.
          "Operation beeing validated" corresponds to a operation from your bank operations, but
          which has not been received by the bank yet;
          "Validated operation" corresponds to an operation from your bank operations.

        - @{b}Predefined operations@{ub}:
          Some operations are predefined. To choose them you must use the lower cycle gadget.
          (all those operations are validated)
          - If you select "@{b}borrowing@{ub}", you'll be asked the interest rate and the number of
          monthly payement. An automatic operation will be created after that and it will attend
          to the lending repayment. You'll be able to modify, erase or obtain informations aobut
          your borrowing.
          (see the chapter @{"opérations automatiques" LINK "Outils" 30}).
          N.B: If you enter a negative amount for the borrowing it means that you are the praetor !!

        - If you choose "@{b}deposit/withdrawal@{ub}", a deposit or a withdrawal operation will be
          created according to the operation amount sign. A deposit / withdrawal is a money transfer
          from your account to your pocket.

        - If you choose "@{b}transfer@{ub}", a transfer will be done automaticallyt from your
          account to another one in memory. If there is no other account in memory you will not be
          able to do this transfer...

   - @{b}Cut@{ub} : Erases selected lines and put them into the buffer (only available in
           selection mode)

   - @{b}Copy@{ub} : copies selected lines to the buffer (only available in selection mode)

   - @{b}Paste@{ub} : recopies buffer lines to the current account. So it is possible to copy lines
             from one account to another very quickly. (only possible if the buffer is not empty)

   - @{b}Paste and move@{ub} : Same as "Paste" but you can select lines to move in accordance
                      to days, months and years. So you can copy lines without having to change
                      the date after the operation. (only available if the buffer is not empty)

   - @{b}Account@{ub} : opens a window to ask user some informations about current account :
              ( also available if you click on bank icon or the one below )

       - titular name;

       - account number;

       - account type;

       - starting balance;

       - bank name (choose it from a list)

       - account kind (choose it from a list) . Examples : office, family, club ...

   - @{b}Category@{ub} : With BlitzBank, you can sort your operations according to their
                category, so you can edit your categories :
                A window opens and some buttons pop up. Those buttons allow you to add a category to
                a list, to erase one, to sort categories has you want, to sort them alphabetically or
                to use categories list from another account in memory.
                (also possible with the second gadget )

   - @{b}Password@{ub} : allows you to use a password (enter it twice for more security) . If
                you forget it you'll not be able to enter your account anymore. If you are not sure, don't use it
                and the program will not ask you at startup.

   - @{b}Recalculate balances@{ub} : allows you to recalculate balances from the beginning. This
                            option allows you to be sure not to have errors in your balance calculations. In fact
                            despite a lot of tests, errors are still possible.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Matériel" "Matériel Nécessaire"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}4.Required equipments@{ub}@{uu}

  BlitzBank should work on every Amiga with system 2.0+, @{b}1,6 Mb of free memory.@{ub}
  2 Mb are still advised and the following libraries must be in your LIBS: directory :
    - reqtools.library
    - diskfont.library
    - mathtrans.library
  Localization only works from system 2.1.

   It is necessary for some functions (like automatic standing over / deposit) to have a clock or to
  enter date before starting. I was not able to test BlitzBank with AmigaDOS 2.0 or 2.1 neither
  with the  68000. But ECS chipset works fine since BlitzBank works with a A2030 and ROM3.1.
  If you notice any anomaly on some configurations, you would be kind to @{"contact the author" LINK "Bugs"}
  so the corrections can be done.

  Here are the configurations which proved to work with BlitzBank:
    - A1200 AGA ROM 3.0 or 3.1
    - A1200 AGA + every accelerator boards or memory extension + ROM 3.0 or 3.1
    - A2000 ECS + 68020 + ROM 3.1 + 5Mb
    - A2000 ECS + 68030 + ROM 3.1 + 5Mb
    - A4030 AGA ROM 3.0 or 3.1 + 6Mb
    - A4040 AGA ROM 3.0 + 32 Mb
    - A500 ECS + 68030 + 4Mb + ROM 3.1
    - A1200 + 68030 + ROM 2.0 (Remapping)
    - A1200 + 68060 + ROM 3.1

  Here are those which didn't work with version 2.30 but which may work from now :
    - A600 ECS 68000 + 2Mb
    - A600 ECS 68000 + 5Mb
    - A3000 ECS + 68030 + 6Mb + ROM 3.1

  About the A3000, I have been able to use Blitzbank for 5 minutes on an A3000. Unfortunately, I didn't
  see the exact configuration and if Blitzbank works fine.
  It looks like BLitzbank dosen't work on 68000 computers. I don't know the exact reason for this
  problem and I don't know anybody having an Amiga with a 68000 processor with enough memory to debug
  my program.
  If you own a computer with 68000 processor, install SetPatch version 40. This version corrects lots
  of bugs and especially the 80000003 guru which happened when starting BLitzbank with 68000 CPU. I
  don't know if it corrects all problems but if you experience it, please contact me.

  If somebody knows any other configuration which works / crash with BlitzBank please write to me.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Enregistrement" "Modalités d'enregistrement"
@TOC "MAIN"
