@ENDNODE

@NODE "Projet" "Projet"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}3.Description des menus
3.1 Project@{ub}@{uu}

   - @{b}Open new@{ub}: opens a new account.

   - @{b}Load@{ub} : Loads an account in place of the current account.
            Also recognizes ABank files format.

   - @{b}Open and load@{ub} : opens a new account and loads one at this place.
                         Also recognizes ABank files format.

   - @{b}Insert@{ub} : Insert account lines into the current account. All the account
              characteristics are preserved. The two accounts categories merge (if the
              total number of categories is greater than 150 then some categories will be lost).

     This option is very useful if you decide to create a file for each year for example. You'll just
     have to merge all your files in one to obtain the global statistic for all your account years.
     (Keep in mind the fact that current account characteristics are preserved. So the starting
     balance, logos, password etc will be those from the current account and not those from first
     account)

   - @{b}Save@{ub} : saves the current account with his current name. A .bak file containing
              the old version of the account will be created.

   - @{b}Save as@{ub} : saves the current account with a filename requester. A .bak file
               with the old version will be created.

   - @{b}Import QIF@{ub} : Allows to import QIF files format (accepted by Quicken and MS Money)
                  in current account. If the current account doesn't have any operation, the
                  starting balance will be taken in the QIF file, otherwise it is preserved.
                  The sub-categories of QIF file are ignored. If imported account is from type
                  cash account operations will be automatically be taken as cash operations
                  (by the way not validated).
                  If the imported account if from type bank account, operations will be taken as bank
                  operations (by the way validated).

   - @{b}Export QIF@{ub} : Allows you to save your account with QIF format so you'll be able to
                  use it with Quicken or MS Money. If you choose this option, a requester will ask
                  you for a filename. If the filename doesn't have the QIF extension, two files will
                  be created :

                  - a file FileName_1.QIF which contains bank operations.

                  - a file FileName_2.QIF which contains cash operations.

             When you'll import those files in Quicken or MS Money, choose to import the first one
             as a bank account and the second one as a cash account.
             While BlitzBank allows to have cash and bank money (in a same account or in several
             shared accounts), Quicken and MS Money do it in a separate way (in an account named
             cash account).

   - @{b}Close@{ub} : closes the current account.

   - @{b}User@{ub} : Gives user informations.

   - @{b}About@{ub} : Gives informations about Blitzbank version.

   - @{b}Iconify@{ub} : Allows BlitzBank's iconification. An icon appears on the Workbench
               screen and you can place it where you want. You can come back to BlitzBank
               by selecting "uniconify" in this icon menu. You can save the icon position
               by saving your preferences in "Preferences" menu. If you click on icon
               "close gadget", you'll be asked if you want to uniconify or quit. If you
               choose to quit, you'll be asked if you want to save accounts in memory that
               have been modified after last saving.

   - @{b}Quit@{ub} : Quit BlitzBank. You'll be asked if you want to save accounts in memory
            that have been modified after last saving.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Outils" "Tools"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}3.3 Tools@{ub}@{uu}

  - @{b}Statistics@{ub} : This function displays a pie-chart graphic describing your operations
                 according to their categories. Three cyclic buttons allow you to choose what
                 you want to be considered in the graphic (credits or just debits for example).
                 You can also choose to display only a special period. Example: if you select
                 "1995" and "year", you'll have year 1995 statistics.
                 If you choose "ALL" and "January", you'll have statistics for all January
                 months from all your accounts. If you choose "ALL" and "year", you'll have
                 statistics for all your account years, and as a result your account statistics
                 from beginning to the end.
                 You can save either the window or the pie-chart in IFF format with the
                 corresponding button.
                 You can also print those statistics by clicking the printing button.
                 Since version 1.5, you can directly choose desired month with a menu.
                 This function is available from the pie-chart gadget.

  - @{b}Yearly balance@{ub} : displays a stick graphic showing your credits and debits during
                     twelve consecutive months (you have to choose year and month with the use
                     of cyclic cells). If you choose january 1995, the display will start at
                     january 1995 to end in december 1995.
                     You can choose which operations will be considered for the calcul using a
                     window with ultra-selective filters like with @{"display filters" LINK "Préférences" 14}.
                     You can save the diagram with IFF format clicking on the icon "Save IFF".
                     You can also do a graphic printing of this statistics clicking on the print
                     button.
                     This function is available from the gadget representing a stick graphic.

  - @{b}Automatic operation@{ub}: In BlitzBank, an automatic operation authorizes you to
                         enter all datas for a normal operation and its frequency. You will
                         then see it appear automatically when needed without doing anything !
                         BlitzBank allows you to add, modify and erase automatic
                         standing over / payment.
                         Those two functions arre available with the help of two gadgets.

    - @{b}Add@{ub} : You can add an automatic operation like a normal operation but you can
            also define the period for the operation. If you choose 010195 as the starting
            date and weekly as the period, the operation will appear the 010195 and then
            automatically inserted every 7 days ! You can moreover choose the number of
            operations, telling Blitzbank how many times the operation must appear in the
            account. if you choose 7 and monthly, the operation will appear automatically
            every month during 7 months. If you choose 0, the number of operations is unlimited.
            You can also choose a predefined automatic operation like withdrawal,etc...
            Finally, you can choose payment amount with the gadget "?" at the right side of
            "credit \ debit". If you select this gadget, the computer will ask you for each
            deduction the amount you want to use with a default value equal to the
            credit / debit amount you entered.
            If you click "Cancel" no operation will appear.
            Attention, if you select this option for a transfer, the computer will ask you the
            amount for each account. Actually, it was necessary because an automatic transfer
            creates an automatic operation in the two concerned accounts.

    - @{b}Modify \ Erase@{ub} : you can modify, erase or obtain informations on an automatic
                       operation by choosing it in the cycling cell and then clicking on "modify",
                       "erase" or "information".
                       If you choose @{b}info@{ub}, a window will pop up giving you precious
                       informations about your automatic operation like the number of transfers
                       still to do and their total cost, ...
                       If you choose @{b}erase@{ub}, this operation will be erased.
                       If you choose @{b}modify@{ub}, the same window as below will appear and
                       you'll be able to modify what you want. ( the displayed date corresponds
                       to the date of the next deduction / transfer ). If you modify an automatic
                       transfer, you will be asked to enter the destination account in memory.
                       If the account choosen is not the good one, BlitzBank will tell you and
                       nothing will be changed.

  - @{b}Previsional budget@{ub} : By using this option, you can predict your expenses and incomes
                 for each category and for the next year.
                 Previsional budget window contains categories list, the year of the financial
                 exercise and a table. The table indicates the amount you provided for expenses
                 and for incomes, the amount you received or spent, and the gain or the loss you
                 made. This is possible for each month of the exercise and for the category you
                 choosed. Only one yearly budget is in memory so if you change the year for the
                 exercise, only the column for realized amounts will be affected.
                 In brief, you can compare the budgetary forecast with several years of account
                 but the budget will not change (you can always save each yearly budget and load
                 the one you need).
                 To edit your expectations, just click on the number to modify and change it like
                 you want (all spaces will be erased so 10 00. 00 will become 1000.00).
                 You can also edit yearly amount directly. If you do this, this sum will be equally
                 shared between all months.
                 The line named "past" indicates the total for the past months. Past months are
                 written in bold characters while future months are written with no style (the
                 current month is not a past month).
                 This line is very useful to know if you are correct with your budget.
                 To obtain the global budget of the year you just have to select "all categories"
                 in the list. In this case, no editing will be accepted.
                 Previsional budget is automatically saved with the account so "save" and "load"
                 gadgets are only useful if you want to conserve budgetary forecast from a previous
                 year or another prevision to consult it later.
                 Attention, the saved budget is only valid for for the account it comes from because
                 it depends on its categories. If you load a budget in an account which doesn't have
                 the same categories, sums will not coincide.

  - @{b}Impression@{ub} : Allows printing of your account with a filter. Like this, you can choose
                 to print any period, just credits, just one category, or lines with a certain kind
                 of characters string...
                 Altough you can use Workbench"Printer" preferences (clicking on the gadget
                 'Use preferences'), you can also set the number of lines and columns printable per
                 sheet and the paper type (continuous or not).
                 You can save those settings using "Preferences" menu.
                 Selection of printing filters is made like for display filters.

  - @{b}Import Logos@{ub} : You can integrate your own bank logos or account types in Blitzbank.
                   The window owns 4 buttons. You must first load a picture (ILBM format). Then if
                   the colors are not the good ones, You can click on the button 'Remap Logo' to make
                   the picture compatible with Blitzbank's palette. After that, you just have to save
                   the logo and to choose his type (bank or account). You must give a name to the logo.
                   If this name already exists, the logo will replace the old one. Otherwise a new logo
                   will take place in logos list. You must absolutely save the logo in the default
                   directory, otherwise Blitzbank will not save the logo.

  - @{b}Help@{ub} : This function permits you to consult the Amigaguide documentation as a background
           task. You can also do this with the HELP key.
           In order that it works, Amigaguide documentation has to be in the directory indicated after
           the tooltype "HELPDRAWER" from BlitzBank icon.
           The program then starts default tool from Blitzbank.guide with this argument. The icon
           default tool must be valid.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Préférences" "Preferences"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}3.5 Preferences@{ub}@{uu}

  - @{b}Screen Mode@{ub} :
        - Under the heading "Initially", you can either choose to use a default
          screenmode or to select a screenmode while loading Blitzbank.
        - Under the heading "now", you will find an icon that permits you to select
          screenmode immediately. This operation doesn't affect preferences. Color number will always
          be 16, whatever the screenmode is.

  - @{b}Choose Palette@{ub} :
        Allows to change the four first palette colors and to choose colors display for credits,
        debits, deposits / withdrawals and comments.
        N.B.: Comments are operations with null amount.

  - @{b}Date Format@{ub} :
        You can choose between several date formats :
                020295 , 02.02.95 , 02-02-95 , 02/02/95 , 02 fev 95

  - @{b}Display@{ub} :
          This powerful function allows you to choose account lines that you want to see in the
        principal screen, by hiding those which doesn't correspond to your preferences.
          You can for example just display one month's operations, or more precisely credits
        operations from category "lambda" and which can be found in may 1994 !! You can go back to
        a normal display with the "normal" button.
          Credits and debits total amounts displayed in the top left corner are relative to the lines
        displayed.

  - @{b}Separate Thousands@{ub} : You can display numbers with thousands separator or not.

  - @{b}Progression@{ub} :
        This option allows to use a status bar display during long operations like account insertion
        and statistics display.

  - @{b}Share Pocket@{ub} :
        If selected, it permits pocket amount calculation on all your accounts in memory
        (it is the sum of all the pockets).
        It is useful for those who do cash operations between several accounts.

  - @{b}Add Pocket@{ub}:
        If selected, this option allows to take pocket into consideration in the real balance
        calculation.
        If selected, real balance = bank balance + pocket + operations beeing validated.
        If not selected, real balance = bank balance + operations beeing validated.

  - @{"Search" LINK "Recherche"} :
        - Maj=Min : if selected, you can do researches without taking capital letters into
                    consideration.
     - Replace the line : if selected, it permits to replace the complete line which contains the
                          desired element. Otherwhise, it only replaces what has been found.

  - @{b}Hide Soms@{ub} :
        Hides all current account sums if selected.
        Useful if you don't want a visitor to see your account amounts.

  - @{b}Load Module@{ub} :
        Loads a module with a file requester. This module will be tested to see if it has
        Pro/Noise/SoundTracker format and will be played if the "play module" option is choosen.

  - @{b}Play Module@{ub} :
        Plays Pro/Noise/SoundTracker module previously loaded. If no module has
        been loaded, the program will directly go to "load module" option.

  - @{b}Save preferences@{ub} :
        Saves preferences and iconification icon place and number of lines and columns for printing.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Recherche" "Search"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}3.4 Search@{ub}@{uu}

  - @{b}Search@{ub} : asks for a character string and search fot it in the current account.

  - @{b}Search Again@{ub} : continues a research that has been stopped.

  - @{b}Replace By@{ub} : asks a character string and replaces the string found previously
                 by the one you choosed or replaces the line to which the string belongs
                 according to the preference you choosed in the @{"Preferences" LINK "Préférences" 40} .

  - @{b}Replace@{ub} : replaces the string found previously by the current replacement string
              or replaces the line to which the found string belongs according to what
              preference you choosed in the wished preference in the menu @{"Preferences" LINK "Préférences" 40} .

@ENDNODE

@NODE "légal" "Legal stuff"
@TOC "MAIN"
@{b}@{u}1.2 Legal stuff@{ub}@{uu}

   Despite numerous tests, some bugs may still exist.
   If you use this program, I will not be responsible for any direct or indirect damages caused by
   the use of BlitzBank. you use BlitzBank at your own risks !

   BlitzBank is freely distributable. Only the keyfile received by the user must NEVER be copied.
   Registered user will be responsible if his keyfile is disclosed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Ventilations" "Spreads"

@{b}@{u}4. Spreadings
4.1 What is a spreading ?@{ub}@{uu}

A spreading is an operation that allows you to bring several operations together.
Example: A friend gives you a 1500 FF check. This check is in fact the result of a 500 FF repayment
         for a previous loan, plus an advance of 600 FF and another repayment of 400 FF. You can then
         create a spreaded operation that will be considered as one operation for your account, but
         you'll be able to see the details creating the three previous spreaded operations.

A spreaded operation is an operation included in a spreading.
A spreaded operation can contain :
            - its own amount (you can draw a positive and a negative amount for spreaded operations
              of a same spreading)
            - its own category (it will be used in statistics and filters).
            - its own designation.

Of course a spreading can hold a big number of spreaded operations. spreading amount is always equal
to the sum of all spreaded operations.

See the chapter "@{"spreading creation" LINK "createventil"}".
@ENDNODE


@NODE "createventil" "Spreading creation"

@{b}@{u}4.2 Creation and modification of a spreading@{ub}@{uu}

To create a spreading you have two possibilities :
        - either you create a predefined operation "spreading" as explained in the part
          "@{"add an operation" LINK "éditer" 11}".
        - or you choose an operation already created and you click on its category (verify that
          you are in modification mode). Click then on "spreading" and a spreading operation will
          be substituted to this operation.
          This operation amount will be lost and you'll have to enter all necessary spreaded
          operations ( see the chapter "@{"Creation of a spreaded operation" LINK "createsousventil"}".

If you want to transform a spreading in a normal operation, click on this spreading category column
when it has no spreaded operation, choose the category and click on "Ok".
A spreading can be modified like any other operation:

         - You can change the date. Corresponding spreaded operations will be moved too.

         - You can change the designation.

         - You cannot change its amount by hand because it is calculated automatically.

         - You can change its spreading. All spreading operations have the same validation that their
           spreading. So changing the validation of a spreading modifies the validation of all
           spreaded operations at the same time.

For the manipulation of spreadings, see chapter "@{"Spreading manipulation" LINK "manipventil"}".
@ENDNODE


@NODE "createsousventil" "Creation of a spreaded operation"

@{b}@{u}4.3 Creation and modification of a spreaded operation@{ub}@{uu}

To create a spreaded operation, You have to click on column "debit\credit" of corresponding
spreading. A window pops up that looks like the one for @{"creation of a normal operation" LINK "éditer" 11}".
You only have access to designation field, amount and category, the other fields were known
by the spreading.

A spreaded operation acts the same way as any other operation and you can modify it the way you
like. The creation of a spreaded operation automatically updates the amount of corresponding
spreading. If you decide to change the date of a spreaded operation, this operation will be
"taken out" of the spreading; it means that it'll become a normal operation and the spreadign will
have one spreaded operation less. The amount for the spreading is always updated.
You cannot modify the validation for a spreaded operation, but only the one from the spreading it
belongs to.
@ENDNODE


@NODE "manipventil" "Spreading manipulation"

@{b}@{u}4.4 Spreading manipulation@{ub}@{uu}

A spreading can be displayed with two means:

        - either the spreading is displayed alone and the spreade operations are hidden.
        - or the spreading is displayed with its spreaded operations.

The spreaded operations are always displayed in a non bold text mode and their date is "|".
To change the display you have to click on the spreading category column in modification mode.
You can also make all current account spreaded operations visible / invisibles with the use of
the edit menu options.

When saving account, the visible / invisible state of each spreading will be saved.
@ENDNODE
